President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 5, 2016, as National Day of Prayer in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of prayer in seeking refuge, expressing gratitude, and finding peace in times of uncertainty. It also highlights the role of prayer in inspiring acts of kindness, service to others, and addressing the challenges faced by society. The proclamation calls for the extension of religious freedom to all people and recognizes the need to stand up for those around the world who face fear or violence due to their religion or beliefs. President Obama encourages citizens to give thanks and pray according to their own faiths and consciences, and asks for God's guidance, mercy, and protection as the nation strives for a more just world.